family care and medical leave (fml) is available to eligible employees in accordance with the federal family and medical leave act (fmla), the california family rights act (cfra) and collective bargaining unit agreements. fml may be used for yourself or an eligible family member. upon completion of fml, you are entitled to return to the same or similar position with equivalent benefits, pay and conditions of employment. you are also entitled to retain any health insurance benefits during time away from work due to fml. see the family medical leave (fml) information sheet [pdf] for additional information. complete the certification of qualifying exigency for military family leave (fml) [pdf] and forward to the leave program manager along with the certification of serious injury or illness of covered service member military family leave (fml) [pdf] . complete the return to work certification [pdf] and forward to the leave program manager. you may not return to work without the approval of the leave program manager. for additional information contact up-leaves@sjsu.edu . university-personnel@sjsu.edu up north: 408-924-2450 up south: 408-924-2250  up webmaster up north administration building 242 up south upd building 3rd floor 